title: South Korea election: Government response to coronavirus sees surge in support and high turnout
description: 'They made the best of the virus', says one voter, as country holds world's first election during coronavirus pandemic
content:
South Korean President Moon Jae-ins Democratic Party surged to a majority of seats Wednesday in the Souths fractious National Assembly in the first national elections held anywhere since the coronavirus pandemic swept the world.
